<p>I am trying to print how many times a particular Key has occurred in an array and it seems like it's printing one for all of the values. Could anyone please tell me what logical error I am having in the code below:</p>  <pre><code>import java.util.HashMap; import java.util.Map;  public class MostOccuranceOfNumber {      public static void main(String[] args) {           int[] n = {1,2,3,4,5,6,7,7,7,7};          Map&lt;Integer, Integer&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;Integer,Integer&gt;();          // Create Hash Map          for(int i = 0 ; i &lt; n.length ; i++){               if(map.containsKey(n)){                  map.put(n[i], map.get(n[i]) +1);              }             else{                  map.put(n[i], 1);             }              for(Map.Entry&lt;Integer, Integer&gt; m : map.entrySet()){                  System.out.println("Key "+m.getKey()+"Occured"+m.getValue()+"times");              }           }      }  } </code></pre>